The paper deals with algorithms for low rank approximation of tensors, which involves linear algebra and optimization techniques. This suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), cs.IT (Information Theory), or cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The use of bicriteria and parameterized complexity solutions also suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS or cs.CG sub-categories.
